downloadUrl.name: downloadUrl
downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

pagination.name: pagination
pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

about.name: about
about.description: The subject matter of the content.

gameItem.name: gameItem
gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

departureStation.name: departureStation
departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

musicCompositionForm.name: musicCompositionForm
musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

result.name: result
result.description: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote a book.

vehicleSpecialUsage.name: vehicleSpecialUsage
vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

nextItem.name: nextItem
nextItem.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

recordingOf.name: recordingOf
recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

audienceType.name: audienceType
audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

interactionService.name: interactionService
interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

targetDescription.name: targetDescription
targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

educationalAlignment.name: educationalAlignment
educationalAlignment.description: An alignment to an established educational framework.

uploadDate.name: uploadDate
uploadDate.description: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

urlTemplate.name: urlTemplate
urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

upvoteCount.name: upvoteCount
upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

sku.name: sku
sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

broadcastChannelId.name: broadcastChannelId
broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

associatedMedia.name: associatedMedia
associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

query.name: query
query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

sameAs.name: sameAs
sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.

funder.name: funder
funder.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

position.name: position
position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

playerType.name: playerType
playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

unitCode.name: unitCode
unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

arrivalAirport.name: arrivalAirport
arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

bestRating.name: bestRating
bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

softwareRequirements.name: softwareRequirements
softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

typeOfGood.name: typeOfGood
typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

numberOfForwardGears.name: numberOfForwardGears
numberOfForwardGears.description:
The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): C62

actionStatus.name: actionStatus
actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

workExample.name: workExample
workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

mileageFromOdometer.name: mileageFromOdometer
mileageFromOdometer.description:
The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.

Typical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles

permissions.name: permissions
permissions.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

provider.name: provider
provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

screenCount.name: screenCount
screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

openingHoursSpecification.name: openingHoursSpecification
openingHoursSpecification.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

occupancy.name: occupancy
occupancy.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person

saturatedFatContent.name: saturatedFatContent
saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

availabilityStarts.name: availabilityStarts
availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

encoding.name: encoding
encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

interactivityType.name: interactivityType
interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

gamePlatform.name: gamePlatform
gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

orderItemStatus.name: orderItemStatus
orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

programMembershipUsed.name: programMembershipUsed
programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

trackingUrl.name: trackingUrl
trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

processorRequirements.name: processorRequirements
processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

grantee.name: grantee
grantee.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

membershipNumber.name: membershipNumber
membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

recipeYield.name: recipeYield
recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

qualifications.name: qualifications
qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role.

gameServer.name: gameServer
gameServer.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

arrivalPlatform.name: arrivalPlatform
arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

bed.name: bed
bed.description:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

availableDeliveryMethod.name: availableDeliveryMethod
availableDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

accessibilitySummary.name: accessibilitySummary
accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."

workFeatured.name: workFeatured
workFeatured.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

recipeCategory.name: recipeCategory
recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipe—for example, appetizer, entree, etc.

fatContent.name: fatContent
fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

character.name: character
character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

areaServed.name: areaServed
areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

postOfficeBoxNumber.name: postOfficeBoxNumber
postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

audience.name: audience
audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

awayTeam.name: awayTeam
awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

providesService.name: providesService
providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

instructor.name: instructor
instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the CourseInstance.

sourceOrganization.name: sourceOrganization
sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

remainingAttendeeCapacity.name: remainingAttendeeCapacity
remainingAttendeeCapacity.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

mpn.name: mpn

memberOf.name: memberOf
memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

isPartOf.name: isPartOf
isPartOf.description: Indicates a CreativeWork that this CreativeWork is (in some sense) part of.

actor.name: actor
actor.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

defaultValue.name: defaultValue
defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

beforeMedia.name: beforeMedia
beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

actionOption.name: actionOption
actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

broadcastTimezone.name: broadcastTimezone
broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts

partOfSeries.name: partOfSeries
partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

includedInDataCatalog.name: includedInDataCatalog
includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

workLocation.name: workLocation
workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

coverageStartTime.name: coverageStartTime
coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

busName.name: busName
busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

vehicleInteriorColor.name: vehicleInteriorColor
vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

browserRequirements.name: browserRequirements
browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

floorSize.name: floorSize
floorSize.description:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard

appliesToPaymentMethod.name: appliesToPaymentMethod
appliesToPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

departureBusStop.name: departureBusStop
departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

bitrate.name: bitrate
bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

netWorth.name: netWorth
netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

videoFormat.name: videoFormat
videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

ineligibleRegion.name: ineligibleRegion
ineligibleRegion.description:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.

numberOfEpisodes.name: numberOfEpisodes
numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

requiresSubscription.name: requiresSubscription
requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription (either paid or free). Allowed values are true or false (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

minValue.name: minValue
minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

actionApplication.name: actionApplication
actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

trailer.name: trailer
trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or tv/radio series, season, episode, etc.

steeringPosition.name: steeringPosition
steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

arrivalGate.name: arrivalGate
arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

loanTerm.name: loanTerm
loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

target.name: target
target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint for an Action.

includedComposition.name: includedComposition
includedComposition.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

line.name: line
line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

minPrice.name: minPrice
minPrice.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

regionsAllowed.name: regionsAllowed
regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in ISO 3166 format.

priceRange.name: priceRange
priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example $$$.

gtin8.name: gtin8
gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

image.name: image
image.description: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

endDate.name: endDate
endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

annualPercentageRate.name: annualPercentageRate
annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

hasDeliveryMethod.name: hasDeliveryMethod
hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

flightNumber.name: flightNumber
flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

itemListElement.name: itemListElement
itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

paymentUrl.name: paymentUrl
paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

greater.name: greater
greater.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

artMedium.name: artMedium
artMedium.description: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

partOfEpisode.name: partOfEpisode
partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

orderStatus.name: orderStatus
orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

prepTime.name: prepTime
prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in ISO 8601 duration format.

recordLabel.name: recordLabel
recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

agent.name: agent
agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.

reservationStatus.name: reservationStatus
reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

validFor.name: validFor
validFor.description: The time validity of the permit.

incentiveCompensation.name: incentiveCompensation
incentiveCompensation.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

reviewRating.name: reviewRating
reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The reviewRating applies to rating given by the review. The aggregateRating property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

jobTitle.name: jobTitle
jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

propertyID.name: propertyID
propertyID.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

appliesToDeliveryMethod.name: appliesToDeliveryMethod
appliesToDeliveryMethod.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

targetProduct.name: targetProduct
targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

subOrganization.name: subOrganization
subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

dateRead.name: dateRead
dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

publisher.name: publisher
publisher.description: The publisher of the creative work.

workHours.name: workHours
workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

broadcastServiceTier.name: broadcastServiceTier
broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

startTime.name: startTime
startTime.description:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

isrcCode.name: isrcCode
isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

hasOfferCatalog.name: hasOfferCatalog
hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

additionalType.name: additionalType
additionalType.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

valuePattern.name: valuePattern
valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

publication.name: publication
publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

underName.name: underName

broadcastAffiliateOf.name: broadcastAffiliateOf
broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

vehicleEngine.name: vehicleEngine

text.name: text
text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.

deathPlace.name: deathPlace
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

loser.name: loser
loser.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

smokingAllowed.name: smokingAllowed
smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

globalLocationNumber.name: globalLocationNumber
globalLocationNumber.description: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

vehicleModelDate.name: vehicleModelDate
vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

expires.name: expires
expires.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.

videoFrameSize.name: videoFrameSize
videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

publishedOn.name: publishedOn
publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

numberOfDoors.name: numberOfDoors
numberOfDoors.description:

deliveryStatus.name: deliveryStatus
deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

dataFeedElement.name: dataFeedElement
dataFeedElement.description: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

coursePrerequisites.name: coursePrerequisites
coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another Course or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using AlignmentObject.

characterAttribute.name: characterAttribute
characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

albumProductionType.name: albumProductionType
albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

amountOfThisGood.name: amountOfThisGood
amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

checkinTime.name: checkinTime
checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

resultReview.name: resultReview
resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

unsaturatedFatContent.name: unsaturatedFatContent
unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

numberedPosition.name: numberedPosition
numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

billingAddress.name: billingAddress
billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

maximumAttendeeCapacity.name: maximumAttendeeCapacity
maximumAttendeeCapacity.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

birthPlace.name: birthPlace
birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.

parentService.name: parentService
parentService.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

typicalAgeRange.name: typicalAgeRange
typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

codeRepository.name: codeRepository
codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, github, CodePlex).

vehicleConfiguration.name: vehicleConfiguration
vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

endTime.name: endTime
endTime.description:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

billingPeriod.name: billingPeriod
billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

gender.name: gender

isLiveBroadcast.name: isLiveBroadcast
isLiveBroadcast.description: True is the broadcast is of a live event.

numChildren.name: numChildren
numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

hoursAvailable.name: hoursAvailable
hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

iataCode.name: iataCode
iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

predecessorOf.name: predecessorOf
predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

departurePlatform.name: departurePlatform
departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

pickupTime.name: pickupTime
pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pickup a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

parentItem.name: parentItem
parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

broadcastDisplayName.name: broadcastDisplayName
broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

printColumn.name: printColumn

arrivalBusStop.name: arrivalBusStop
arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

bccRecipient.name: bccRecipient
bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

fuelType.name: fuelType

availability.name: availability

vehicleIdentificationNumber.name: vehicleIdentificationNumber

partySize.name: partySize

priceSpecification.name: priceSpecification

providerMobility.name: providerMobility
providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

releasedEvent.name: releasedEvent

educationalUse.name: educationalUse

itemReviewed.name: itemReviewed

stepValue.name: stepValue

fuelConsumption.name: fuelConsumption
fuelConsumption.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.

schemaVersion.name: schemaVersion
schemaVersion.description: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

dateSent.name: dateSent
dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

accessibilityFeature.name: accessibilityFeature
accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

dateIssued.name: dateIssued
dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

aggregateRating.name: aggregateRating
aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

subtitleLanguage.name: subtitleLanguage
subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in IETF BCP 47 standard format.

alternativeHeadline.name: alternativeHeadline
alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

recipeIngredient.name: recipeIngredient
recipeIngredient.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

trainName.name: trainName
trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

locationCreated.name: locationCreated
locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

recipeInstructions.name: recipeInstructions
recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

value.name: value
value.description:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.

  • For QuantitativeValue and MonetaryAmount, the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
  • For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.

inAlbum.name: inAlbum
inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

isConsumableFor.name: isConsumableFor
isConsumableFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

accessModeSufficient.name: accessModeSufficient
accessModeSufficient.description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.

itemListOrder.name: itemListOrder
itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

artform.name: artform
artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

temporalCoverage.name: temporalCoverage
temporalCoverage.description: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

codeSampleType.name: codeSampleType
codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

eligibleTransactionVolume.name: eligibleTransactionVolume
eligibleTransactionVolume.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

equal.name: equal
equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

subEvent.name: subEvent
subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

blogPost.name: blogPost
blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

accountablePerson.name: accountablePerson
accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

homeLocation.name: homeLocation
homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

nutrition.name: nutrition
nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

embedUrl.name: embedUrl
embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.

partOfSeason.name: partOfSeason
partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

interestRate.name: interestRate
interestRate.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

partOfOrder.name: partOfOrder
partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

totalPrice.name: totalPrice
totalPrice.description: The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

inPlaylist.name: inPlaylist
inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

identifier.name: identifier
identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.

availableAtOrFrom.name: availableAtOrFrom
availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

maxPrice.name: maxPrice
maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

countryOfOrigin.name: countryOfOrigin
countryOfOrigin.description: The country of the principal offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie or program.

tickerSymbol.name: tickerSymbol
tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we reccommend using the controlled vocaulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO15022.

scheduledPaymentDate.name: scheduledPaymentDate
scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

lodgingUnitDescription.name: lodgingUnitDescription
lodgingUnitDescription.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

duns.name: duns
duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

jobBenefits.name: jobBenefits
jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

gameLocation.name: gameLocation
gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

hasMenu.name: hasMenu
hasMenu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

taxID.name: taxID
taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

courseMode.name: courseMode
courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

spatialCoverage.name: spatialCoverage
spatialCoverage.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

followee.name: followee
followee.description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

recipe.name: recipe
recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

lyricist.name: lyricist
lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

feesAndCommissionsSpecification.name: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
feesAndCommissionsSpecification.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

reservationFor.name: reservationFor
reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant,etc. being reserved.

priceCurrency.name: priceCurrency
priceCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

serviceLocation.name: serviceLocation
serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

executableLibraryName.name: executableLibraryName
executableLibraryName.description: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

trainNumber.name: trainNumber
trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

sugarContent.name: sugarContent
sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

catalogNumber.name: catalogNumber
catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

answerCount.name: answerCount
answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

offers.name: offers
offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

editor.name: editor
editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

discussionUrl.name: discussionUrl
discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

coverageEndTime.name: coverageEndTime
coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

numberOfPreviousOwners.name: numberOfPreviousOwners
numberOfPreviousOwners.description:
The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.

Typical unit code(s): C62

artworkSurface.name: artworkSurface
artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

issueNumber.name: issueNumber
issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

customer.name: customer
customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

petsAllowed.name: petsAllowed
petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

artEdition.name: artEdition
artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

award.name: award
award.description: An award won by or for this item.

streetAddress.name: streetAddress
streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

containsSeason.name: containsSeason
containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

category.name: category
category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

contactOption.name: contactOption
contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

claimReviewed.name: claimReviewed
claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

pageEnd.name: pageEnd
pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

expectedArrivalFrom.name: expectedArrivalFrom
expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

makesOffer.name: makesOffer
makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

instrument.name: instrument
instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.

orderQuantity.name: orderQuantity
orderQuantity.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

priceValidUntil.name: priceValidUntil
priceValidUntil.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

givenName.name: givenName
givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

ticketNumber.name: ticketNumber
ticketNumber.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

valueMaxLength.name: valueMaxLength
valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

cholesterolContent.name: cholesterolContent
cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

creditedTo.name: creditedTo
creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

datePosted.name: datePosted
datePosted.description: Publication date for the job posting.

runtimePlatform.name: runtimePlatform
runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (Example - Java v1, Python2.3, .Net Framework 3.0).

skills.name: skills
skills.description: Skills required to fulfill this role.

copyrightHolder.name: copyrightHolder
copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

paymentStatus.name: paymentStatus
paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

characterName.name: characterName
characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

breadcrumb.name: breadcrumb
breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

dependencies.name: dependencies
dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

branchCode.name: branchCode
branchCode.description:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

broker.name: broker
broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

addOn.name: addOn
addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

sportsTeam.name: sportsTeam
sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

featureList.name: featureList
featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

accessibilityHazard.name: accessibilityHazard
accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

albumReleaseType.name: albumReleaseType
albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

copyrightYear.name: copyrightYear
copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

sportsEvent.name: sportsEvent
sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

actionPlatform.name: actionPlatform
actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

distance.name: distance
distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

issn.name: issn
issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

hasMap.name: hasMap
hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

printEdition.name: printEdition
printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

opponent.name: opponent
opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

releaseOf.name: releaseOf
releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

participant.name: participant
participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.

educationRequirements.name: educationRequirements
educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position.

servicePostalAddress.name: servicePostalAddress
servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

warranty.name: warranty
warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

includesObject.name: includesObject
includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

eligibleQuantity.name: eligibleQuantity
eligibleQuantity.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

priceComponent.name: priceComponent
priceComponent.description: This property links to all UnitPriceSpecification nodes that apply in parallel for the CompoundPriceSpecification node.

ccRecipient.name: ccRecipient
ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

significantLink.name: significantLink
significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

applicationSubCategory.name: applicationSubCategory
applicationSubCategory.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

recordedAt.name: recordedAt
recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

recordedAs.name: recordedAs
recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

additionalProperty.name: additionalProperty
additionalProperty.description:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

serviceOutput.name: serviceOutput
serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

commentCount.name: commentCount
commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

relatedLink.name: relatedLink
relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

replacee.name: replacee
replacee.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

replacer.name: replacer
replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

reportNumber.name: reportNumber
reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

winner.name: winner
winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

articleSection.name: articleSection
articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

tool.name: tool
tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

fileFormat.name: fileFormat
fileFormat.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

validUntil.name: validUntil
validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

typeOfBed.name: typeOfBed
typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

inLanguage.name: inLanguage
inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

familyName.name: familyName
familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

fuelEfficiency.name: fuelEfficiency
fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.

track.name: track
track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

seeks.name: seeks
seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

member.name: member
member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

touristType.name: touristType
touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. eg. Children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

suggestedMaxAge.name: suggestedMaxAge
suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximal age recommended for viewing content.

yearlyRevenue.name: yearlyRevenue
yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

episodeNumber.name: episodeNumber
episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

boardingGroup.name: boardingGroup
boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

lesser.name: lesser
lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

playMode.name: playMode
playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

dissolutionDate.name: dissolutionDate
dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

requiredMinAge.name: requiredMinAge
requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

arrivalStation.name: arrivalStation
arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

reviewCount.name: reviewCount
reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

contentUrl.name: contentUrl
contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

circle.name: circle
circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

availableLanguage.name: availableLanguage
availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage

performerIn.name: performerIn
performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

question.name: question
question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

numberOfItems.name: numberOfItems
numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

isGift.name: isGift
isGift.description: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

referencesOrder.name: referencesOrder
referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

validFrom.name: validFrom
validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

box.name: box
box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

sportsActivityLocation.name: sportsActivityLocation
sportsActivityLocation.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

subReservation.name: subReservation
subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

advanceBookingRequirement.name: advanceBookingRequirement
advanceBookingRequirement.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

baseSalary.name: baseSalary
baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

foodEvent.name: foodEvent
foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

accessibilityAPI.name: accessibilityAPI
accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

boardingPolicy.name: boardingPolicy
boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

honorificPrefix.name: honorificPrefix
honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

specialOpeningHoursSpecification.name: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
specialOpeningHoursSpecification.description:
The special opening hours of a certain place.

Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

byArtist.name: byArtist
byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.name: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
isAccessoryOrSparePartFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

additionalName.name: additionalName
additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

passengerSequenceNumber.name: passengerSequenceNumber
passengerSequenceNumber.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

addressCountry.name: addressCountry
addressCountry.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

toLocation.name: toLocation
toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

interactionStatistic.name: interactionStatistic
interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

seatSection.name: seatSection
seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

validThrough.name: validThrough
validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

recipient.name: recipient
recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

attendee.name: attendee
attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

successorOf.name: successorOf
successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

amenityFeature.name: amenityFeature
amenityFeature.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

contentRating.name: contentRating
contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

starRating.name: starRating
starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

applicationCategory.name: applicationCategory
applicationCategory.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

geoRadius.name: geoRadius
geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

dropoffLocation.name: dropoffLocation
dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

lastReviewed.name: lastReviewed
lastReviewed.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

athlete.name: athlete
athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

requiredCollateral.name: requiredCollateral
requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

isVariantOf.name: isVariantOf

publishingPrinciples.name: publishingPrinciples
publishingPrinciples.description:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via URL) a document describing the editorial principles of an Organization (or individual e.g. a Person writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a CreativeWork (e.g. NewsArticle) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language, sometimes related information (e.g. indicating a funder) can be expressed using schema.org terminology.

sponsor.name: sponsor
sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

producer.name: producer

productionDate.name: productionDate

interactionType.name: interactionType

numberOfPlayers.name: numberOfPlayers

dateDeleted.name: dateDeleted

valueAddedTaxIncluded.name: valueAddedTaxIncluded

acquiredFrom.name: acquiredFrom
acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

openingHours.name: openingHours
openingHours.description:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

  • Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: Mo, Tu, We, Th, Fr, Sa, Su.
  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.
  • If a business is open 7 days a week, then it can be specified as <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Mo-Su">Monday through Sunday, all day</time>.

numTracks.name: numTracks
numTracks.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

expectsAcceptanceOf.name: expectsAcceptanceOf

game.name: game

location.name: location

toRecipient.name: toRecipient

greaterOrEqual.name: greaterOrEqual
